import React, { useState } from "react"; import Header from "../components/parts/header.tsx"; import Footer from "../components/parts/footer.tsx"; export default function ToolsPage() { // State for the commander calculator const [commanderLevel, setCommanderLevel] = useState(1); const [targetLevel, setTargetLevel] = useState(60); const [currentXP, setCurrentXP] = useState(0); const [calculatedXP, setCalculatedXP] = useState(0); const [calculatedSculptures, setCalculatedSculptures] = useState(0); // State for the resource calculator const [troops, setTroops] = useState(100000); const [troopTier, setTroopTier] = useState(5); const [days, setDays] = useState(30); const [calculatedFood, setCalculatedFood] = useState(0); const [calculatedWood, setCalculatedWood] = useState(0); const [calculatedStone, setCalculatedStone] = useState(0); const [calculatedGold, setCalculatedGold] = useState(0); // Commander XP calculator const calculateCommanderXP = () => { // This is a simplified calculation - in a real app you'd have more accurate formulas const baseXP = 1000; const levelFactor = 1.5; const xpNeeded = Math.round(baseXP * Math.pow(targetLevel, levelFactor) - baseXP * Math.pow(commanderLevel, levelFactor) - currentXP); const sculptures = Math.ceil(xpNeeded / 1000); // Simplified calculation setCalculatedXP(xpNeeded); setCalculatedSculptures(sculptures); }; // Resource calculator const calculateResources = () => { // Simplified calculation - in a real app you'd have more accurate formulas const tierMultiplier = Math.pow(1.5, troopTier - 1); const dailyFood = Math.round(troops * 10 * tierMultiplier); const dailyWood = Math.round(troops * 8 * tierMultiplier); const dailyStone = Math.round(troops * 5 * tierMultiplier); const dailyGold = Math.round(troops * 3 * tierMultiplier); setCalculatedFood(dailyFood * days); setCalculatedWood(dailyWood * days); setCalculatedStone(dailyStone * days); setCalculatedGold(dailyGold * days); }; return (
